ent to lead the firm’s portfolio company operations mr weber will work closely with and advise the management and boards of bluemountain portfolio companies and will be responsible for leading the operational oversight governance and value enhancement of those investments he will work closely with portfolio managers engaged in bluemountain’s private capital  opportunistic investments effort mr weber will report to bluemountain ceo  cocio andrew feldstein and cocio derek smith “jon brings to bluemountain a wealth of experience leading the operational oversight and corporate governance efforts of companies across a number of industries” said mr feldstein “his expertise in improving the operational efficiency financial performance and governance of public and private companies will further enhance our ability to deliver returns and value to our investors” “i am incredibly excited to join a firm i’ve always held in high esteem bluemountain is an innovative and talentrich organization with a great portfolio of operating company investments” said mr weber “it’s an exciting time for this strategy and i look forward to collaborating with our investment team and the leadership at our portfolio companies to identify opportunities for growth” prior to joining bluemountain mr weber headed similar efforts at anchorage capital group goldman sachs special situations group and icahn enterprises over the past  years he has served as a board chair member senior executive or board level advisor for dozens of companies in a broad range of industries previously he was an investment banker at jpmorgan chase  co and morgan stanley earlier in his career he also worked as an attorney for weil gotshal  manges he is a life member of the council on foreign relations and a board member of chai lifeline an organization dedicated to meeting the needs of seriously ill children jon earned a jd cum laude from harvard law school and a bs and mba magna cum laude from babson college about bluemountain 